FishList.Name: Çupra
FishList.Description: Çupra, also known as sea bream, is a popular fish in Mediterranean cuisine. It has a mild, sweet flavor and is often grilled or roasted with herbs and olive oil.

FishList.Name: Levrek
FishList.Description: Levrek, or sea bass, is a versatile and delicious fish with tender white flesh. It's commonly pan-fried or baked with lemon and herbs for a delightful taste.

FishList.Name: Somon
FishList.Description: Somon, also known as salmon, is prized for its rich, pink flesh and high omega-3 fatty acids. It's often grilled, smoked, or used in sushi.

FishList.Name: Alabalık
FishList.Description: Alabalık, or trout, is a freshwater fish with a delicate flavor. It's commonly prepared by grilling, pan-frying, or baking.
